    <p>The Trading Education Certificate (TEC) is our own proprietary educational programme, developed and delivered alongside Credit Suisse, which aims to provide our members with the technical knowledge to help kick-start a career in finance. To learn more about the TEC, click <a href="/tec">here</a>.</p>
    <h2>Trading Competition</h2>
    <p>The ICFS is working with Markit to deliver a real-time trading simulation with live market prices across a range of asset classes; from equity indices and government bonds, to currencies and commodity contracts. This initiative puts you in the deep end and allows you to learn by doing. Some of the biggest investment banks use this very simulation to train their new traders and hone their trading techniques. Previous trading experience is absolutely not a prerequisite for this. We encourage everyone to use this as a learning experience, whether you're completely new to trading or if you already have a track record in the industry. Taking part in this trading game whilst taking the TEC course alongside it will help equip you with not only the theory but also the practical knowledge about finance to help you excel in interviews, assessment centres and ultimately the internships themselves.</p>
